recent_articles.title: Tesla stock rises despite sales miss, Microsoft to cut 9K jobs
recent_articles.summary:
Yahoo Finance's John Hyland takes a closer look at some of the top stories on Wall Street as part of today's Market Minute.

Investors are shrugging off the latest ADP report showing an unexpected decline in job growth for June.

Tesla (TSLA) stock is climbing despite the company reporting a 13% drop in vehicle deliveries in its second quarter.

Microsoft (MSFT) plans to cut 9,000 jobs in its second major workforce reduction this year.

Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

recent_articles.title: Centene, Microsoft, Paramount: Trending Tickers
recent_articles.summary:
Centene (CNC) stock is plummeting after the health insurer withdrew its 2025 profit guidance, citing lower market growth and high Medicaid costs.

Microsoft (MSFT) is reportedly planning to cut over 9,000 jobs, according to the Seattle Times, adding to layoffs earlier this year as part of a broader workforce reduction.

Paramount (PARA) agreed to a $16 million settlement with former President Trump over a lawsuit alleging election interference related to an interview of former Vice President Kamala Harris.
